notes.text: a. At Visit 1, a 24-hour Ambulatory ECG will be obtained.
b. A chest x-ray will be obtained at Visit 1 if one has not been done in the previous 12 months.
c. A CT or MRI scan will be obtained at Visit 1 if one has not been done in the previous 12 months.
d. At Visit 1, the Hachinski Ischemia Score will be administered.
e. A blood sample will be obtained at Visit 1 for Apo E genotype determination.
f. For women of childbearing potential only.

h. Blood samples will be obtained at Visits 3, 4, 5, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, and 12. At Visit 3, the sample will be obtained prior to the first dose of study drug. At Visits 4, 5, 7, 8, 9, 10, 11, and 12, the sample will be obtained prior to that day's dose of study drug.
